# PROJECT HEALTH CHECK

## When to Run
- Every 5th session (roughly once per week at 10–20 hrs/week)
- Any time Ryan asks "how are we doing?" or "are we on track?"
- At the start of a session after a milestone is hit

## How to Trigger
Check PATCH_NOTES.md — if the last health check was more than 5 sessions ago, run it before starting work. Otherwise skip.

## Health Check Questions

Ask and answer each of these. Keep answers to one sentence each.

1. **On track?**
   Compare current phase progress to ROADMAP_TIMELINE.md. Are we at or ahead of pace?

2. **Any flags overdue?**
   Check PROJECT_CONTEXT.md Known Flags. Any unresolved flag older than 2 weeks? Name it.

3. **Any rules that need tightening?**
   Check LESSONS_LEARNED.md and POSTMORTEM_TEMPLATE.md. Any pattern that keeps repeating? Name it.

4. **Upcoming deadline pressure?**
   Is a phase deadline or milestone test within the next 4 weeks? Flag it.

5. **Content pipeline healthy?**
   Are content assets (JSON, audio scripts, lore) keeping ahead of code needs? Flag any gap.

## Output Format

Report the health check results to Ryan as a short block:

---
**PROJECT HEALTH CHECK**
- Pace: [On track / Ahead / Behind — one sentence]
- Top open flag: [Name it or "none overdue"]
- Rule to tighten: [Name it or "none identified"]
- Deadline pressure: [Name it or "none in next 4 weeks"]
- Content pipeline: [Healthy or gap identified]
---

Then ask what Ryan wants to work on. Do not assume.

## Reuse Notes
- Keep this rule always-on across projects.
- Update the "When to Run" frequency if the session cadence changes significantly.
